The time has come to tear down our bedroom. The last room in the house where nothing was done, just a little decoration.
Remove the horrible electric heater and the fireplace. Enclose the chimney, replace the damaged plaster and sand it down. Build a custom wardrobe.
You always start with a quick pencil sketch...
The dirty step is finished.
I found several dead birds at the back of the chimney; all dried up :(
Ready for plastering next week
Happy with the small niche on the side
Insert the new closet here (it's not like we've already started drawing it 🙈)
Oh, look what we found behind the radiator!
And even thought about adding a charming little vent to prevent the chimney from getting damp.
The chimney sweep took care of installing the hat and the windbreak. That should be a bit safer for the crows nesting up there 🪺
The plastering is done. We'll install the floor tomorrow!
The rubber underlayment is laid down, I improvised a wood shavings extractor using a toilet paper roll as an accessory for the vacuum 😂
Part of the planks are sorted and ready to lay. We just take a tea break.
Well, progress was slow today because of very delicate cuts around the door posts to achieve a smooth transition into the corridor (which is also being installed now). @user45@twitter.com cursed me.
Done, but on the knees! Bonus: the unpalatable instructions for assembling the new bed. We're going to sleep well tonight!
The floorboards in the hallway and all the baseboards remain to be done. The decorator is coming in a month, so in the meantime, at home, it's chic plaster without any finishing touches.
Small evening do-it-yourself session to remove the lower sections of the door stiles using a tenon saw or a chiseling knife at the spot where the floor should be perfectly fitted.
The cork underlayment of the corridor is also laid.
We finished the corridor floor yesterday! Then left at 5 a.m. this morning to pick up Thing 1 at Heathrow, followed by a nap and the final stretch for the corridor; baseboards installed. We'll take care of the sealing once the glue has dried.
